      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Panorama photograph of a large building essentially designed in the Moorish Revival architectural style. There are people on the street in front of, and around, the building.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The Synagogue was built for the Bulgarian capital's mainly Sephardic Jewish community. The planning architect was Austrian-born Friedrich Grünanger. It was officially opened on 9 September 1909 in the presence of Tsar Ferdinand I of Bulgaria.</ab>
